# Caesar Cipher Decryption using Machine Learning

## Project Overview
This project breaks the Caesar cipher using a simple RNN-based machine learning model. The goal is to predict the shift key by learning character sequences.

## Method
- Character embedding + RNN (PyTorch)
- Predict next character in encrypted text sequences
- Cross-entropy loss for training

## Dataset
Synthetic texts generated from English phrases, encrypted with random Caesar shifts.

## Results
- Training loss decreased over 10 epochs
- Short texts (<10 characters) are more likely to be misclassified (Error Analysis)

